      other effects outside the worm, and it takes 21 (6d6) acid damage at the start
      of each of the worm''s turns.'
    category: Actions
  - name: other
    value: 'f the worm takes 30 damage or more on a single turn from a creature inside
      it, the worm must succeed on a DC 21 Constitution saving throw at the end of
      that turn or regurgitate all swallowed creatures, which fall prone in a space
      within 10 feet of the worm. If the worm dies, a swallowed creature is no longer
      restrained by it and can escape from the corpse by using 20 feet of movement,
      exiting prone. '
    category: Actions
